### Test Authentication API
### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api

### 1. Register a new business user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "marie@coiffure.fr",
  "password": "Password123",
  "firstName": "Marie",
  "lastName": "Dupont",
  "phone": "0612345678",
  "businessName": "Coiffure Marie"
}

### 2. Login with registered user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "marie@coiffure.fr",
  "password": "Password123"
}

### 3. Refresh token (replace with actual refreshToken from login response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### 4. Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 5. Try to register with existing email (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "marie@coiffure.fr",
  "password": "Password123",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "phone": "0612345679",
  "businessName": "Test Business"
}

### 6. Try to login with wrong password (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "marie@coiffure.fr",
  "password": "WrongPassword"
}
